cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.NE, cs.PL 

The paper introduces a new probabilistic logic programming language that incorporates deep learning through neural predicates. This work involves the integration of general-purpose neural networks and expressive probabilistic-logical modeling and reasoning, which suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-categories. Specifically, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it involves program induction and learning from examples, cs.LG (Machine Learning) because it incorporates deep learning, cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it involves natural language processing, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it involves neural networks, and cs.PL (Programming Languages) because it introduces a new programming language.
